        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 24 at 3:33PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 333 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Arden, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Robert Lee, Bronte, Orient, San Angelo State Park, E.V. Spence
Reservoir Near Paint Creek Recreation Area, Water Valley, Grape
Creek, Carlsbad, Broome, Sanco, Arden, Tennyson, The Intersection Of
Highway 208 And Ranch Road 2662, The Intersection Of Highway 158 And
Ranch Road 2059, and Us-87 Near The Coke-Tom Green County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
